{"type":"invariant","iteration":13,"id":"sk-design-five-mode-boundary","statement":"sk-design remains a five-mode hub: interface, foundations, motion, audit, and md-generator; the hub stays logic-free and mode logic belongs in packets.","sources":[".opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:15",".opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:23",".opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:81",".opencode/skills/sk-design/mode-registry.json:14"]}
{"type":"finding","iteration":13,"id":"ledger-all-nine-plugins","summary":"The definitive ledger classifies ui-design, interaction-design, visual-critique, and selected design-systems material as in scope; prototyping-testing, design-ops, and designer-toolkit are narrow/adjacent; design-research and ux-strategy are upstream/out of scope.","sources":[".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/README.md:63",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/README.md:69",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/README.md:77",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/024-designer-skills-research/research/iterations/iteration-001.md:20"]}
{"type":"finding","iteration":13,"id":"visual-critique-best-first-adoption","summary":"The highest-leverage Q4 item is a visual-critique dimension crosswalk inside audit, not a new critique mode or parallel score system.","target":"design-audit/references/critique_hardening.md","leverage":"high","effort":"low-medium","sources":[".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/visual-critique/README.md:3",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/024-designer-skills-research/research/iterations/iteration-006.md:19",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/024-designer-skills-research/research/iterations/iteration-006.md:37"]}
{"type":"finding","iteration":13,"id":"interface-flow-floor-second-priority","summary":"The second adoption priority is a compact interface UX quality-floor expansion for forms, search, navigation, feedback/error proximity, first-run/empty states, and optional flow path wording.","target":"design-interface/references/design-process/ux_quality_reference.md","leverage":"high","effort":"medium","sources":[".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/024-designer-skills-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:17",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/024-designer-skills-research/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:55",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/024-designer-skills-research/research/iterations/iteration-008.md:15"]}
{"type":"finding","iteration":13,"id":"audit-hardening-bundle-third-priority","summary":"The third adoption priority is an audit hardening bundle: component completeness, localization stress, accessibility modality coverage, and token/evidence guards.","targets":["design-audit/references/anti_patterns_production.md","design-audit/references/accessibility_performance.md","design-audit/references/evidence_capture.md"],"leverage":"high","effort":"medium","sources":[".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/024-designer-skills-research/research/iterations/iteration-006.md:45",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/024-designer-skills-research/research/iterations/iteration-007.md:14",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/024-designer-skills-research/research/iterations/iteration-009.md:53"]}
{"type":"finding","iteration":13,"id":"motion-state-machine-fourth-priority","summary":"The fourth adoption priority is a motion state-machine fragment plus small loading and gesture refinements; this fits motion pattern cards and does not justify an interaction mode.","target":"design-motion/assets/motion_pattern_cards.md","leverage":"high","effort":"low-medium","sources":[".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/024-designer-skills-research/research/iterations/iteration-002.md:23",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/024-designer-skills-research/research/iterations/iteration-002.md:91"]}
{"type":"finding","iteration":13,"id":"foundations-layout-fifth-priority","summary":"The fifth adoption priority is foundations layout refinement: grid contract, density-mode spacing, and containment restraint.","target":"design-foundations/references/layout/layout_responsive.md","leverage":"high","effort":"low","sources":[".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/024-designer-skills-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:27",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/024-designer-skills-research/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:35"]}
{"type":"observation","iteration":13,"id":"design-systems-remaining-gap-closed","summary":"The remaining unclassified design-systems skills mostly confirm exclusions: pattern-library and documentation-template are documentation systems, naming-convention is a lint/governance practice, and accessibility-audit duplicates existing audit posture rather than adding a new lane.","sources":[".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/design-systems/skills/pattern-library/SKILL.md:9",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/design-systems/skills/naming-convention/SKILL.md:11",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/design-systems/skills/accessibility-audit/SKILL.md:9",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/design-systems/skills/documentation-template/SKILL.md:9"]}
{"type":"ruled_out","iteration":13,"id":"no-workflow-suite-import","summary":"Do not import designer-skills-main commands as sk-design workflows; source commands chain skills into complete jobs, while sk-design owns mode-routed design judgment.","sources":[".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/README.md:113",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/README.md:117",".opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:21"]}
{"type":"ruled_out","iteration":13,"id":"no-research-strategy-testing-ops-modes","summary":"Do not add research, strategy, testing, design-ops, QA, governance, adoption, rationale, presentation, case-study, or negotiation modes; these exceed taste-led build/visual scope unless reduced to an observable UI check.","sources":[".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/design-research/README.md:3",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/ux-strategy/README.md:2",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/024-designer-skills-research/research/iterations/iteration-008.md:54",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/024-designer-skills-research/research/iterations/iteration-009.md:29"]}
{"type":"ruled_out","iteration":13,"id":"no-parallel-audit-score","summary":"Do not import visual-critique's pass/minor/major ratings as a second scoring system; keep P0-P3 and five audit dimensions as the final audit contract.","sources":[".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/024-designer-skills-research/research/iterations/iteration-006.md:37"]}
{"type":"ruled_out","iteration":13,"id":"no-evidence-overclaims","summary":"Do not claim conversion, confidence, findability, behavior, business impact, or user-impact metrics without supplied baseline, experiment, test, or metric evidence.","sources":[".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/024-designer-skills-research/research/iterations/iteration-008.md:39",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/024-designer-skills-research/research/iterations/iteration-009.md:14"]}
{"type":"finding","iteration":13,"id":"new-mode-judgment","summary":"No new sk-design mode is justified. Visual critique strengthens audit; interaction-design splits into motion/interface/audit; design-systems splits into foundations/audit/motion; no cluster has distinct intent, output contract, and ownership beyond existing modes.","decision":"no_new_mode","sources":[".opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:28",".opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:96",".opencode/skills/sk-design/mode-registry.json:14",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/024-designer-skills-research/research/iterations/iteration-006.md:35"]}
